news.title: Office space leasing falls 4% to 25 million sq ft during Jan-Sep: CBRE
news.para: "Space take-up of 25 million square feet recorded in 2021 YTD (year-to-date), a marginal drop of 4 per cent year-on-year," CBRE said.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC halts construction activities at 54 sites, imposes fine
news.para: The corporation halted construction and demolition activities at sites of 54 private properties on Monday, where "violations of NGT norms were noticed," it said.

news.title: Kaisa Group says trying to solve liquidity issues, pleads for 'more time & patience'
news.para: Kaisa Group said in a statement on its official WeChat account that it was accelerating asset disposals in Shanghai and Shenzhen and using the proceeds for repayments, as well as accelerating its sales of existing properties.

news.title: Cash-strapped Evergrande raises $144 million before payment deadline
news.para: Evergrande sold a 5.7 percent stake totalling HK$1.12 billion ($144m) in HengTen Networks Group in three separate transactions from last Thursday, Hong Kong stock exchange filings showed.

news.title: Spanish property developer Neinor Homes in talks to buy Via Celere
news.para: Via Celere reported gross asset value (GAV) of 1.62 billion euros ($1.87 billion) in July, which would provide a significant boost to Neinor's market share and land bank. Neinor's GAV stood at 2.19 billion euros for the same reporting period.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate appoints KG Krishnamurthy as independent director
news.para: Krishnamurthy, who is former managing director & CEO of HDFC Property Ventures, will be designated as non-executive chairman of the company with effect from February 1, 2022.

news.title: China state council think-tank met builders, banks as debt woes mount, says source
news.para: Participants at the meeting, which took place on Monday, included China Vanke, Kaisa Group, Ping An Bank, China Citic Bank, China Construction Bank and CR Trust, according to the source.

news.title: Over 1,400 homes registered in Mumbai during first week of November
news.para: The property consultant said that the city recorded 10-year best property sale registrations of 8,576 units in October 2021, up 8 per cent from the same month last year.

news.title: Over 1,000 may lose land for first phase of Bhopal Metro
news.para: A resettlement action plan (RAF) estimates Rs 292 crore estimates as compensation for land acquired for the project. The RAF is for two routes — Purple Line (from Karond intersection to AIIMS Bhopal) and Red Line (from Bhadbada Square to Ratnagiri).

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out 300 seats to Operative in Pune
news.para: Operative had also recently signed 300 seats workspace with it in Bengaluru. 315Work Avenue plans to add another 5 lakh sq ft office space over a period of six months.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body's master plan-2041 gets government nod
news.para: ​The VMRDA had first issued a notification of the draft perspective plan-2051 and draft master plan-2041 on June 15 by giving 30 days’ time (from June 16 to July 15) for the public to submit their objections and suggestions.

news.title: Nagpur civic body plans to construct Metro Mall in 30 months
news.para: Recently, the NMC had shortlisted a private agency which has agreed to pay Rs10 crore more than the bid amount of Rs45 crore.

news.title: Mumbai: Fire prevention measures must in buildings, says BMC
news.para: ​​“(It is a must) to furnish a certificate, ie Form B, issued by a licensed agency, twice a year -- January and July – (mentioning that these facilities are maintained and in an) efficient condition,” the BMC said in a statement.

news.title: Minister puts onus of property tax data on Thiruvananthapuram corporation
news.para: LSG minister M V Govindan, in his reply in the ongoing assembly session, said that the software fails to reflect information on tax, which has been paid, because the staff concerned do not post the payments promptly.

news.title: Aurangabad administration firm on razing 328 quarters in labour colony
news.para: While refusing to give any concrete assurance to the residents, Desai said, “As already different courts have given rulings in this case, it will be inappropriate for me to say anything on the issue.”
